The paper deals with the performance analysis of a multiuser system with distributed receive antennas, which is a typical problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of MMSE and ZF receivers also suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SI). The term "macrodiversity" in the title indicates a possible interest in wireless communication systems (cs.MA), and the analysis of symbol error rate for M-PSK or M-QAM modulations suggests a focus on communication theory (cs.COM).
